Author: University of Minnesota PreCalculus Dept.
Reviewed/Remixed by: Doenet team

About the problem: Determine the type of symmetry (symmetric with respect to x-axis, symmetric with respect to y-axis, or symmetric with respect to origin...) given the graph of a function that is symmetric with respect to the origin. 

*************************************************************-->
<problem>
<setup>
<function name="f">arctan(x)</function>
<function name="g1" domain="[0,infinity)">arctan(x)</function>
<function name="g2" domain="[0,infinity)" styleNumber="8">arctan(-x)</function>
<function name="g3" domain="[0,infinity)" styleNumber="8">-arctan(-x)</function>
</setup>

<!--******************************************************
            Begin testing
*******************************************************-->
<!-- <p>f(x) = $f</p>
<p>g1(x) = $g1</p>
<p>g2(x) = $g2</p>
<p>g3(x) = $g3</p> -->
<!--******************************************************
            End testing
*******************************************************-->

  
<p>What is the symmetry of the following graph?</p>
<me>f(x) = $f</me>
<graph xmin="-3" xmax="3" ymin="-1.4" ymax="1.4">
 $f
</graph>

<!--*********************************************
            User solution input
**********************************************-->  
<answer name="ans1">
  <choice>Symmetric with respect to the <m>x</m>-axis</choice>
  <choice>Symmetric with respect to the <m>y</m>-axis</choice>
  <choice credit="1">Symmetric with respect to the origin</choice>
  <choice>All of the above</choice>
  <choice>None of the above</choice>
</answer>


