<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->  
<solution>
  <p>Symmetric with respect to the origin (or <term>odd symmetry</term>). This means that the following statement holds:
  <me>f(x) = -f(-x)</me>
  </p>
  <p>You can imagine this by visualizing two transformations in your mind.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><alert>First transformation:</alert> a reflection across the <m>y</m>-axis (imagine the graph is on a piece of paper that is folded over at its vertical axis)
  <graph displayYAxis="false" displayXAxis="false" size="small" xmin="-3" xmax="3" ymin="-1.4" ymax="1.4">
    $g1 $g2
    <line styleNumber="13" fixed>x=0</line>
    <ray styleNumber="5" fixed endpoint="(0,0)" direction="(1,0)"/>
    <ray styleNumber="6" fixed endpoint="(0,0)" direction="(-1,0)"/>
    <legend position="lowerleft">
      <label><m>f(x)</m></label>
      <label><m>f(-x)</m></label>
    </legend>
    <vector name="v" fixed styleNumber="5" tail="(-1,1)" head="(-0.4,1)"/>
    <label anchor="$v.tail" positionFromAnchor="upperright">Fold</label>
  </graph>  
    </li>
    <li>
  <p><alert>Second transformation:</alert> a reflection across the <m>x</m>-axis (imagine the paper is folded once more across its horizontal axis). If these two functions directly overlap, then the function is symmetric with respect to the origin.</p>
    <graph displayYAxis="false" displayXAxis="false" size="small" xmin="-3" xmax="3" ymin="-1.4" ymax="1.4">
      $g1 $g3
      <ray styleNumber="13" fixed endpoint="(0,0)" direction="(0,1)"/>
      <ray styleNumber="13" fixed endpoint="(0,0)" direction="(1,0)"/>
      <ray styleNumber="6" fixed endpoint="(0,0)" direction="(-1,0)"/>
      <ray styleNumber="6" fixed endpoint="(0,0)" direction="(0,-1)"/>
      <legend position="lowerleft">
        <label><m>f(x)</m></label>
        <label><m>-f(-x)</m></label>
      </legend>
      <vector name="v2" fixed styleNumber="5" tail="(0.8,-0.8)" head="(0.8,-0.4)"/>
      <label anchor="$v2.tail + (0.1,0.1)" positionFromAnchor="right">Second Fold</label>
    </graph>  
    </li>
  </ul>
</solution>
</problem>



